Fluoroalkanes (RF) and fluorohalogenoalkanes (RFX) are useful because of the following properties:

* Chemically **inert** due to **strong** C-F bond.
* RF and RFX with small alkyl groups have **low** boiling points and so are easily vapourised. (they can be kept as liquid at high pressure and released as gas at atmospheric pressure).
